===Etymology===
{{NL.}} term ''[[anarchia]]'' < {{Gr.}} [[αναρχία]] < [[α-|αν-]] (without), + [[ἀρχός]] (ruler, authority).

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈænərki/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|anarchies|-}}

# Absence of [[hierarchy]], [[power]] and [[authority]].
# Absence of any form of political authority or [[government]].
# Political disorder and confusion.
# A rejection of imposed morality from any governing body.
# Self-government.
# A government without a ruler.
# A society without rules or laws.
# Without rules or laws (synonyms: [[anomie]], [[anomy]]).
# Confusion, chaos, disorder.

'''Note:'''  As [[w:Anarchism|anarchists]] use it, "anarchy" does not imply chaos or [[anomie]], but rather a harmonious anti-authoritarian society. In fact, anarchist conceptions of such a society (such as those of [[w:Anarcho-syndicalism | anarcho-syndicalists]]) often include a high degree of societal structure.

